<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-EMMITTQ&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EMMITT SMITH SAYS HE'S FOCUSED ON THIS SEASON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RAY BUCK 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
WICHITA FALLS, Texas _ Emmitt Smith knows how to hold court.
Minutes after the Cowboys' morning workout at Midwestern State
University ended yesterday, the NFL's leading active rusher stood
in the middle of the practice field and talked 20 minutes about
what's on his mind, as well as what he tries to keep off his mind.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Recent retirements of Michael Irving and Daryl ``Moose''
Johnston have left him feeling, well, like there has been a death
in the family. He has grieved. He has mourned. He now is moving on.
</P>
<P>
   But when you're Emmitt Smith, with 13,963 career rushing yards
after 10 seasons with the Cowboys and you have only Walter Payton
(16,726) and Barry Sanders (15,269) ahead of you on the NFL's
all-time rushing list, you're careful not to get ``too'' far ahead.
</P>
<P>
   Smith needs 1,307 yards to pass Sanders, who remains retired
after coming to that decision a year ago this month, and 2,764
yards to pass Payton for the NFL record ... but Smith says his mind
is on this day, this camp, this season, and nothing beyond that.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Dave Campo said yesterday that the emphasis on the
Cowboys' passing attack with off-season acquisitions of Joey
Galloway and Jackie Harris to complement Rocket Ismail shouldn't
pre-empt the notion that the Cowboys will be an Emmitt Smith
running team again in 2000.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have some weapons in the throwing game, but I don't want
anyone to get the impression that we're not going to be a running
football team,'' Campo said. ``Because to win, we have to be able
to run the football and be a physical, power-running football
team.''
</P>
<P>
   Smith, 31, doesn't know what to expect as far as his number of
carries or his number of touches in what is a return of the
Cowboys' old Super Bowl offense with some modifications. He is
coming off his busiest season (329 carries, 1,397 yards) since
1995, and that included missing 10 quarters because of hand and
groin injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Here is what Smith had to say:
</P>
<P>
   Question: How tough has it been to watch three-time Super Bowl
championship teammates such as Irvin and Johnston retire?
</P>
<P>
   Answer: ``It's been tough. People might think that it's hard to
get close to people when you're in the business of a revolving
door, but you do get close and then players like Daryl and Michael
retire. I mean, it lets you know the reality that your day is
coming. Do y'all pick up on the key word that these \Rretired\S
guys use? ``Family.'' Well, now it's like a person in your family
has just died. In reality, they move on to the real world. But in
the sports world, they're with you in spirit, but they're no longer
with you in body.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: So, what do you do?
</P>
<P>
   A: ``What do you do when somebody dies in your family? You go in
mourning, then eventually you pick yourself up and move forward.
I'm picking myself up and moving on.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: Is there comfort in seeing No. 8 _ Troy Aikman _ still in the
huddle?
</P>
<P>
   A: ``Yes, some comfort. But we're coming down to the last of the
Mohicans.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: Erik Williams' agent is now saying that Williams is
contemplating retirement. What do you make of that, and did you see
if coming?
</P>
<P>
   A: ``All this is new to me. But it's Erik's decision, so let the
man make it. It's not my job to guess or judge if he's making the
right decision. My job is to get here, play football and help this
team win. I hope Erik can get on board with us. And when that day
happens, it's up to him to be prepared. Right now, I'm not going to
worry about it too much.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: How much do you think about breaking Walter Payton's record?
</P>
<P>
   A: ``That's down the road. I'll just take it one day at a time
and keep moving toward that mark.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: You caught 40 to 60 passes per season in the Norv Turner and
Ernie Zampese offenses of the '90s. You're getting back to that
same basic philosophy. Do you anticipate getting more touches this
season?
</P>
<P>
   A: ``In the old system, I got both \Rrushes and catches\S. But I
don't see that happening in this system because I think I'll still
be spared playing on third down.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: What is a realistic goal for the 2000 Cowboys?
</P>
<P>
   A: ``I agree with Troy. Realistically, a goal of going to the
Super Bowl is not something that is unattainable. But it's going to
take a lot of work, a lot of blessings and a lot prayers to stay
healthy.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
