<SLUG> BC-OSTLER-COLUMN-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 LAKER FANS RULE THIS LEAGUE  &HT;     By SCOTT OSTLER 
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Now forming: my new mass-murderer rotisserie league (MML).
</P>
<P>
   It's not as bad as it sounds. A normal rotisserie league works
like this: A group of people, like your canasta club, antes up a
few bucks each and drafts teams from all active players in a given
sport. Each day, you get points based on the performance of your
players in the previous night's games.
</P>
<P>
   Standings are kept. At season's end a champion is crowned and
the pot awarded.
</P>
<P>
   In my MML, each participant drafts several sports franchises.
But it's not seasonal. Your roster might wind up consisting of the
L.A. Dodgers, the French Davis Cup tennis team, the Winnipeg Blue
Bombers, and so on.
</P>
<P>
   You score points when criminal suspects wearing your team's gear
appear in news photos or TV news clips.
</P>
<P>
   Roughly 90 percent of all felony suspects wear team-logo gear
when committing crimes or when apprehended. If The Chronicle runs a
photo of a man robbing a bank while wearing a Dodger cap _ bingo,
points for you.
</P>
<P>
   Bonus points if your team figures into the crime somehow, like a
few years ago when a Raiders fan was robbing banks to pay for his
Raiders tickets.
</P>
<P>
   Points are awarded on a sliding scale based on the severity of
the crime, from mass murder to jaywalking. The maximum score is
100, which would be awarded if someone discovered a photo of Hitler
wearing a New York Yankees cap.
</P>
<P>
   NEWS IN THE NEWS: Restaurant prices rising in the Bay Area,
because of low supply of good servers (so we'll pay more for worse
service). Coffee prices rising, because of freak snowstorm in
Coffeebeanland (can't we just switch to iced coffee?). Gas prices
rising, because the Gas Fairy is feuding with Zeus (I'm making a
mental note to sell the SUV riding mower). Home prices and rents
rising, because rich people are invading Bay Area (``The Greenbacks
are coming!'').
</P>
<P>
   I'm no Greenspan, but I think I detect a trend, folks.
</P>
<P>
   IF YOU'RE going to drive, don't phone, fax, e-mail, channel
surf, surf the Internet and/or play Mortal Kombat.
</P>
<P>
   The National Highway Traffic Safety Administration has
determined that doing all that stuff could be distracting to a
driver.
</P>
<P>
   They have also determined that taking a toaster into the bathtub
could be distracting to a bather.
</P>
<P>
   Shockingly, the mobile-phone industry says ``Pish,''
cell-phoning from a car is perfectly safe, as long as you're not
phoning your wife to get the details of her affair with the Webvan
delivery guy.
</P>
<P>
   The cell phone industry spokesperson quoted by the L.A. Times is
Tom Wheeler. How cute is that?
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Wheeler makes the point that cell phone users can report
accidents quickly. Which is nice, since they cause so many of 'em.
</P>
<P>
   SOME ENGLISH folks are offended by the portrayal of British
brutishness in the movie ``The Patriot.''
</P>
<P>
   The movie, they claim, shows British soldiers committing
atrocities that are more atrocious than the atrocities they
actually committed.
</P>
<P>
   The British are whining! The British are whining!
</P>
<P>
   ANYTHING YOU read here, you can give it the Tom Tolbert
treatment.
</P>
<P>
   Tolbert is co-host of a KNBR sports-talk program. Doug Wilkins
heard Tolbert say, when referring to some baseball statistics,
``You can throw them out the window with a grain of salt.''
</P>
<P>
   GERMANS THROW the book at two criminals! But the book is a very
thin paperback, titled, ``Winning With Honor and Integrity.''
</P>
<P>
   In Germany, a former East German Olympic official and a doctor
have been found guilty of systematically and secretly doping female
Olympic athletes with steroids for at least 15 years.
</P>
<P>
   Talk about your German engineering.
</P>
<P>
   The guilty official was sentenced to 22 months probation; the
guilty doctor to 18 months probation. Because they showed remorse,
they also got their courthouse parking validated.
</P>
<P>
   Their work ruined lives of scads of athletes, caused
birth-defect babies, corrupted the Olympic games, set off a domino
effect wave  &LR; of steroid abuse worldwide, and they get off with ...
probation.
</P>
<P>
   About 20 East German coaches, doctors and others have been
convicted in the decades-long dope-a-thon. The total amount of time
these people will spend in jail or prison: Zip.
</P>
<P>
   In honor of the East Germans, one word will be added to the
official motto of the Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
   ``Swifter, higher, stronger, hairier.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
