<P>
   &UR; HOME (Moved in ``l'' category) &LR;  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HUFFINGTON-POLITICS (Los Angeles) _ Political insiders may
debate the motivations behind the latest evolutionary twist in the
remarkable life of Arianna Stassinopoulos Huffington. This summer,
as the Democratic and Republican parties hold their national
conventions in Philadelphia and Los Angeles, shadow conventions
will convene nearby, providing a running commentary and critique.
Conceived of by Huffington and the Internet impresario Peter
Hirshberg, the conventions' goal is to expose the ``empty
rhetoric'' of the two major parties and ``give voice to millions of
Americans currently shut out of the national debate.'' By Russ
Baker.
</P>
<P>
   ADS-INNUENDO (Undated) _ Same-sex innuendo is showing up more
and more in national advertising, from automobilers, beer and soft
drinks to home furnishings. Marketers call it ``gay vague''
advertising.
</P>
<P>
   HAMPTONS-DAYWORKERS (East Hampton, N.Y.) _ In the summer here,
it is not the homeowners who reign. Underpinning almost every house
is a network of people: the air-conditioning men, the electricians,
the rose pruners, the hedge trimmers, the house watchers. By Tracie
Rozhon.
</P>
