<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ ATLANTA _ Recently I repeated a study that said
consumers would demand that a battery-powered electric vehicle be
approximately $28,000 less expensive than a comparable
internal-combustion vehicle before they would agree to own it. The
survey was sponsored, among others, by Toyota.(Sharp, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
