<P>
   GLF-USWOM-WEBB (Gurnee, Ill) _ Lack of patience, says Aussie
Karrie Webb, has led to her downfall in four tries at women
golfing's biggest tournament. By Michael Madden. 1250 words.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS-BISHOP (Foxborough, Mass.) _ Michael Bishop knows
he will not unseat Drew Bledsoe, but he wants to be in position to
be active every Sunday, a step up from his role of emergency third
quarterback last season. By Nick Cafardo. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   CYC-TOUR-RULES (Lausanne, Switzerland) _ On paper, the Tour de
France waits for no one. The Tour does wait sometimes, though. The
group has to stop for barricaded railroad crossings, the cyclists
skid to a stop for crashes, and they are forced to pause when a
local group is staging a protest. By Susan Bickelhaupt. 950 words.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-RYAN-COLUMN (Boston) _ We've got some basketball royalty
hanging around the Clark Athletic Center at UMass-Boston this week.
By Bob Ryan.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
