   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN(Washington) _ Oklahoma Gov. Frank Keating, said to
be on Texas Gov. George W. Bush's short list for the vice
presidential nomination, is in town promoting his ``marriage
initiative.'' He wants to develop a minimum standard of marriage
preparation that would be stressed in churches and schools. But
this is a sensitive, private issue that may not sell well outside
the conservative South. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
