row in an Arizona penitentiary, is one of thousands of prisoners
now advertising on Web sites for pen pals. He does not mention that
he was convicted in 1996 of killing a man by bashing his head
against rocks. Victims' rights groups say such Web sites inflict
more pain on the families of victims. In the face of such
criticism, the Arizona Legislature has enacted a law that forbids
prisoners from using third-party Internet service providers. And
prison officials in other parts of the country have adopted similar
policies, despite protests by civil libertarians. By Dirk Johnson.
