<P>
   KASHMIR-DESTINY (Baramulla, India) _ For 40 years many people in
India's only Muslim-majority state longed to join Islamic Pakistan.
But after 11 years of a violent pro-Pakistan insurgency, and the
harsh Indian repression it provoked, many who live in Kashmir are
now alienated from both their masters in New Delhi and their
self-proclaimed saviors in Islamabad. By Indira A.R. Lakshmanan.
1600 words.
</P>
