   PROVIDENCE-REVIVAL (Providence, R.I.) _ It was only a few years
ago that Providence regained its rivers by rescuing the Providence
River from under generations of road decking and relocating its
confluence with the Moshassuck and Woonasquatucket that flow into
it at a strategic juncture near a new inner harbor at the cove
called Waterplace Park. So now, in place of polluted waters and a
dead ``downcity,'' as the business district is called, Providence
has become more like those vibrant European cities with rivers
running through them and picturesque bridges joining the two banks.
By Carol Dietz.
</P>
