<P>
   CYBER-APATHY _ If the Internet is the great new democratic
frontier, then its 333 million ``netizens'' might rightfully be
called apathetic. The world's first global cyber-election is slated
to take place this fall, but so far only about 2 percent of all
Internet users have registered to vote. Registration campaigns in
the United States and abroad have drummed up only about 55,000
possible voters. About 750
</P>
