<P>
   VIDEO-FESTIVAL (New York) _ It often seems these days that no
aspect of our private and communal lives is shielded from the
patient, prying lens of the video camera. From amateur pornography
to security surveillance loops, from home movies of weddings,
childbirths and family reunions to C-Span and ``Big Brother,''
video records and shapes what we know of reality. So, what kind of
shape are we in, anyway? One place to look for an answer might be
at the New York Video Festival, which opens tonight and runs at the
Walter Reade theater at Lincoln Center through next Wednesday. By
Carol Dietz.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   ART-EXHIBITS (Undated) _ The fresh crop of shows in museums
outside New York City this summer include several about artists
prominent around the same time: ``Calder in Connecticut'' at the
