IDENTITY-THEFT, JUNK-DNA, BOX-SOUTHFLORIDA ;
</P>
<P>
   Deletes: COX-VETERANS
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-SUMMIT _ THURMONT, Md. _ President Clinton staked a
great deal of diplomatic capital on the Camp David summit. Perhaps
that is why just when everyone _ including White House officials _
thought the talks has fallen apart, he made a daring rescue and
convinced both sides to stay at it in his absence. But what really
happened Wednesday night and the wee hours of Thursday morning? And
where do they go from here? Clinton is still in danger of losing
the one legacy he so desperately wants for his presidency: A
lasting peace in the Middle East. Developing. (Deans, Cox News
Service) 20.
</P>
<P>
   WAN: Location, Atlanta; Category, International; Subcategory,
Other.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving on the NYT wire in (i) International and (w)
Washington categories.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-CHRISTIANS _ JERUSALEM _ While teams primarily of
Palestinian Muslims and Israeli Jews in Camp David battle_ or talk
_ through the fate of Jerusalem, Christians want to remind them
that the Holy Land is theirs, too. The leaders of the three biggest
Christian denominations in Jerusalem _ Roman Catholic, Greek
Orthodox and Armenian Orthodox _ penned a letter this week asking
for representation at Camp David. The request was belated and not
likely to be honored, but it was intended as a reminder that
Jerusalem is the site of Christianity's holiest sites and should be
kept open for Christians. Israeli leaders have brushed off
Christian concerns lately. (Kaplow, Cox News Service) WITH _ Box
listing several of the main Christian sites in Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
   WAN: Location, Atlanta; Category, International; Subcategory,
Other.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving on the NYT wire in (i) International and (w)
Washington categories.
</P>
<P>
   JOURNAL-PATRIOT _ LONDON _ The British reaction to the movie,
The Patriot. To say the least, they're angry at the portrayal of
British soldiers and officers as Nazi-like baby killers and are all
worked up in general about the way Americans treat England.
Moreover, they're miffed that we stupid Americans keep calling it
the Revolutionary War instead of the War of Insurrection.
Developing. (Roughton, Cox News Service) WITH PHOTO (Mug of
Roughton available.)
</P>
