its biggest rivals will be based in Atlanta, the companies said
Thursday. ForestExpress.com, an electronic trading post for paper
and building supplies, will debut in the fourth quarter. The
company expects to hire 150 people and is looking for office space
north of the Perimeter. (Bond, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
