   STEELYDAN-FORMULA _ Call it the Steely Dan formula: a little
soul, a little substance, a little satire. And, of course, all that
jazz. For much of the '70s and early '80s, it was a sound that
defined a creative pop ideal. Even though the duo _ guitarist
Walter Becker, now 50, and keyboardist Donald Fagen, 52 _ had its
share of hits (Reeling in the Years, Do it Again, Peg, Rikki Don't
Lose That Number), this wasn't exactly music for the masses.
(Passy, Palm Beach Post) 45. MOVED.
