<P>
   CYC-TOUR _ Lance Armstrong was none too thrilled about riding
another long stage in the Tour de France. In his eyes, cycling the
152.5 miles between Lausanne, Switzerland and this city at the
entrance of the Black Forest was a tad too long this far into the
race. So Armstrong sat back, rode conservatively and allowed what
few sprinters still left in the Tour to jockey for the stage win.
He finished 34th, 15 minutes and 40 seconds behind stage victor
Salvatore Commesso. He maintained his 5:37 lead over Jan Ullrich.
(Halliburton, Austin American-Statesman) 15-18. WITH PHOTOS.
