   FLA-UNCANDIDATE (Miami) _ ``Don't vote for me,'' pleads a Miami
firefighter who qualified for the city council election in the
suburb of Eastern Ranches, then learned he could lose his job
because Miami forbids city employees to hold office elsewhere. He
has been on the phone, relentlessly pursuing his un-campaign for
the Tuesday election. But it is an uphill battle. Early indications
are that the candidate, a 27-year veteran of the Miami-Dade Fire
Department and a popular figure in his community of about 7,000 to
9,000 people, has been pulling ahead. By Rick Bragg.
</P>
<P>
   MARRIAGE-TAX (Washington) _ House and Senate Republicans have
agreed to send President Clinton the House version of the
``marriage penalty'' tax bill. The somewhat less costly version was
viewed as making a threatened veto more difficult. By Richard W.
Stevenson.
</P>
