<P>
   NET-ENVELOPES _This story takes a look at how the envelope
manufacturing industry, particularly two local companies _ Atlantic
Envelope Co. and World Envelope Manufacturing Inc. _ is responding
to the Internet its impact on their bottom lines since consumers
and businesses are moving toward paperless transactions. While the
need for envelopes won't be going away entirely, manufacturers say
they will have to adapt _ i.e., make the envolpes they produce more
technology inclusive as way of remaining competitive. Even the U.S.
Post Office is jumping on the Internet bandwagon, pushing its own
bill paying service and other web-based initiatives to stave off
possible revunue losses from this medium. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
