<HEADLINE>
A KIIS FOR THE WEB
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVID BLOOM 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
KIISFMi.com: the digital equivalent of Los Angeles broadcast
station KIIS-FM, it is garnering insider raves, with a Webby Award
nomination this spring and trade publication Radio Ink putting the
site at the top of its list of the best Web radio stations. &QL; 
Where: www.kiisfmi.com. &QL; 
What's cool: Four mixes of music _ ``mainstream,'' hip hop, house
and retro _ give you access to a more targeted mix of tunes than
the broadcast side can. &QL; 
Features: A ton of features that show what's possible for for a
site from a commercial broadcast station: a discussion area (though
really insipid); contests, quizzes, news, shopping, horoscopes,
jokes, a shopping and clothes area presided over by hottie DJ Ellen
K, info on the ``iJs'' and of course, the ability to request a song
by e-mail. They also have started a Webcasting operation, FMiTV,
that will carry video from events like the recent Wango Tango
concert. &QL; 
You'll like this if: You want to tune in to what's happening with
commercial broadcast radio on the Net. &QL; 
Think your Web fave is good enough for Site of the Week? Send your
suggestions to davidbloomearthlink.net. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
