<SLUG> BC-GP-WEB0721-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Forest consortium locating in Atlanta
 &HT;    By Patti Bond
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Atlanta will be home to a business-to-business
Internet venture being created by the country's largest forest
products companies.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier this year, Georgia-Pacific Corp. teamed with its two
largest rivals, International Paper and Weyerhaeuser Co., to form
an electronic trading post for pulp, paper and wood products. The
partners said Thursday they had picked a headquarters and a name,
forestexpress.com.
</P>
<P>
   About 80 people will be hired in the next several months, and
the company is looking at office space north of the Perimeter, a
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
   Forestexpress.com, designed to cut costs by making ordering
easier for business customers and suppliers, said it raised $51
million for the venture.
</P>
<P>
   Four other companies _ Boise Cascade, Louisiana-Pacific, Mead
and Willamette _ recently joined as strategic partners.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
