   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MARRIAGE-PENALTY (Washington) _ The House and Senate move ahead
with compromise legislation to eliminate the so-called marriage
penalty on some two-income families. By lowering the amount of the
tax cut, the Republican leadership in Congress hopes to undermine
President Clinton's threatened veto. By STEVE LASH.
</P>
