   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   PRISON-HEAT (Houston) _ During heat waves, prisoners must seek
relief with small fans in their cells. But they can't even do that
in the Houston area. The prison system is selling electricity back
to the local power company during peak times, which means inmates
have no power in their cells during the hottest times of day. By
JAMES KIMBERLY.
</P>
<P>
   MARS (Houston) _ As NASA races to revive its failed Mars
exploration program, scientists are torn over how aggressively to
proceed with new robotic missions to the Red Planet. By MARK
CARREAU.
