<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With INTERNET-SOFTWARE. Moving in (w) Washington and (f)
financial categories for release Sunday, July 23.
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ICANN AT A GLANCE
</P>
<P>
   Name: Internet Corporation for Assigned Names and Numbers.
</P>
<P>
   Founded: First met in November 1998
</P>
<P>
   What it is: A non-profit organization based in California.
</P>
<P>
   Purpose: To take over administration of the Internet address
system from the U.S. government.
</P>
<P>
   Responsibilities: Manage the Internet's root servers; settle
trademark and name disputes; oversee registration of addresses.
</P>
<P>
   Who: The board is composed of 19 people. Nine were selected by
the group's supporting organizations, nine will be elected by the
at-large membership _ open to any Internet user in the world_ and
the board itself appoints a president.
</P>
<P>
   Funding: $4.3 million annual budget comes from fees paid by
companies and countries that have registered their names.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
